Anadolu Cam, BIM, Petrol Ofisi: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-09T07:14:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/anadolu-cam-bim-petrol-ofisi-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 1,084.07, or
1.8 percent, to 61,301.65 yesterday.    Anadolu Cam Sanayii AS (ANACM)  : The Turkish glassmaker
will build a furnace with annual capacity of 120,000 tons in the
city of Bursa, it said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock
Exchange after the market closed yesterday. Anadolu Cam gained 5
kurus, of 1.7 percent, to 2.99 liras.    BIM Birlesik Magazalar AS (BIMAS)  : The Turkish discount
supermarket chain said profit last year rose to 245.6 million
liras from 212.9 million liras in 2009, according to a statement
to the bourse after the close yesterday. The 2010 net income
exceeded an average estimate of 237.4 million liras in a
Bloomberg survey 23 analysts. BIM rose 50 kurus, or 1 percent,
to 51.50 liras.    Petrol Ofisi (PTOFS)  AS: Turkey’s biggest fuel
retailer’s free float dropped to 3.02 percent from 4.28 percent
as OMV AG raised its stake in the company to 96.98 percent from
95.72 percent, Petrol Ofisi said in a statement to the bourse
after the close yesterday. Petrol Ofisi fell 24 kurus, or 3.3
percent, to 7.04 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
